            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> It does play nice with _Neovim's_ builtin comment plugin, though, so I don't see the need for deviating from upstream.\r\n\r\nBecause Neovim's builtin comment plugin works based on comment line instead of comment block. For comment line in PHP, people usually use `// %s` or `# %s` (I think the first is more popular). I have never seen anyone using `/* %s */` for just single line of comment.\r\n\r\nAlso see #29085 . I don't understand the commentstring has been changed for C, why it can't be changed for PHP too?",
