            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Because 1. this change was made in the connection with removing the default (C) commentstring, which was necessary for treesitter injection support in the comment plugin and 2. Neovim is written in C and we don't use `/* */` comments at all (unlike Vim). So that is a very different (and special) situation that does not imply any change in the general policy.\r\n\r\nI don't doubt your claims about PHP comment strings, but you need to convince the filetype maintainer, not us.",
